1244
01:23:25,667 --> 01:23:26,919
Um... "You're my hero."

1245
01:23:27,002 --> 01:23:28,587
You got a secret admirer?

1246
01:23:28,712 --> 01:23:32,007
Secret? (CHUCKLING)
That's not so secret.

1247
01:23:32,090 --> 01:23:34,092
I don't know what
you're talking about.

1248
01:23:34,176 --> 01:23:35,219
Well, um...

1249
01:23:36,386 --> 01:23:40,140
Well, hey, listen, I'm having
a party tonight. Mmm-hmm.

1250
01:23:40,349 --> 01:23:43,644
And I was wondering if you
maybe wanted to come,

1251
01:23:44,728 --> 01:23:46,855
maybe? Yeah? No?

1252
01:23:46,939 --> 01:23:48,440
What's in it for me?

1253
01:23:49,274 --> 01:23:51,276
What's in it for me?
(BOTH LAUGH)

1254
01:23:54,571 --> 01:23:57,366
Yeah. And, um,

1255
01:23:57,449 --> 01:23:59,535
I have something I want to
tell you later. A secret.

1256
01:24:00,118 --> 01:24:01,954
Later? Okay.
Yes. Okay.

1257
01:24:02,621 --> 01:24:04,957
Wait, the "you're my hero"
thing, how did you...

1258
01:24:05,123 --> 01:24:08,252
Thank you for my beautiful rose.
I love it.

1259
01:24:15,676 --> 01:24:18,011
What'd you say to me?
This is not working out.

1260
01:24:19,137 --> 01:24:21,139
Okay, Sam, you can't
break up with me.

1261
01:24:21,265 --> 01:24:26,061
I think I can
and I think I just did.

1262
01:24:29,147 --> 01:24:30,148
I should've picked Elody.

1263
01:24:36,321 --> 01:24:37,489
What just happened?

1264
01:24:37,948 --> 01:24:39,283
<i>ELODY: You guys were
supposed to...</i>

1265
01:24:39,366 --> 01:24:41,410
I mean, you said
you wanted to...

1266
01:24:43,412 --> 01:24:44,997
It's Rob Cokran.

1267
01:24:46,582 --> 01:24:47,749
He doesn't deserve me.

1268
01:24:48,333 --> 01:24:50,168
ELODY: Nonetheless,
very shocking.

1269
01:24:50,294 --> 01:24:52,588
(SIGHS) Sociopath,
12 o'clock.

1270
01:24:52,754 --> 01:24:53,839
ALLY: Uh-Oh.

1271
01:24:53,922 --> 01:24:55,340
LINDSAY: Does it smell
like pee in here?

1272
01:24:55,507 --> 01:24:56,758
(ALL IMITATE STABBING)
Stop.

1273
01:24:56,842 --> 01:24:58,427
Norma Bates!
What?

1274
01:25:00,178 --> 01:25:01,179
Just don't.

1275
01:25:01,513 --> 01:25:02,514
ALLY: But it's Juliet.

1276
01:25:02,848 --> 01:25:05,350
Exactly, it's Juliet.

1277
01:25:05,475 --> 01:25:08,020
She has a name
and she is a person.

1278
01:25:08,353 --> 01:25:09,896
Yesterday, you said
you were afraid

1279
01:25:09,980 --> 01:25:12,024
she would bite you
if she got too close.

1280
01:25:13,859 --> 01:25:15,652
That was
a long time ago.

1281
01:25:18,155 --> 01:25:19,406
That was yesterday.

1282
01:25:24,745 --> 01:25:26,872
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1283
01:25:38,675 --> 01:25:40,636
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

1284
01:25:58,779 --> 01:26:00,906
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

1285
01:26:03,325 --> 01:26:04,326
SAMANTHA: Hey, Linds.

1286
01:26:04,409 --> 01:26:06,244
All right,
well, let's do this!

1287
01:26:06,370 --> 01:26:07,663
Linds.
What?

1288
01:26:08,413 --> 01:26:10,916
How come you never told me
about your parents' divorce?

1289
01:26:10,999 --> 01:26:12,417
(CHUCKLES)

1290
01:26:12,834 --> 01:26:14,002
Are you serious?

1291
01:26:15,420 --> 01:26:16,421
Yeah.

1292
01:26:18,674 --> 01:26:21,760
Why would I talk about something
that happened a thousand years ago?

1293
01:26:23,178 --> 01:26:24,930
Because it happened to you.

1294
01:26:26,098 --> 01:26:27,265
And you matter to me.

1295
01:26:27,432 --> 01:26:28,517
I don't know what
you're talking about.

1296
01:26:28,600 --> 01:26:29,601
Come here.
Okay? Let's go inside.

1297
01:26:29,726 --> 01:26:30,769
Come here.
(EXHALES)

1298
01:26:34,523 --> 01:26:37,609
You know you don't have to
act so tough all the time.

1299
01:26:38,402 --> 01:26:39,403
Mmm.

1300
01:26:43,115 --> 01:26:44,950
Don't worry about me, okay?

1301
01:26:46,493 --> 01:26:47,703
I love you no matter what.

1302
01:26:47,786 --> 01:26:49,121
Let's get inside.
(LAUGHS) Okay.

1303
01:26:50,288 --> 01:26:51,748
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)
Move, move, move.

1304
01:27:00,132 --> 01:27:02,259
Hey, um, you made it.

1305
01:27:02,718 --> 01:27:03,885
Come with me.

1306
01:27:03,969 --> 01:27:05,595
What? Okay.

1307
01:27:07,097 --> 01:27:08,473
What?

1308
01:27:12,728 --> 01:27:15,981
(STAMMERS) I believe
you owe me a secret, right?

1309
01:27:16,106 --> 01:27:17,399
I believe I do.

1310
01:27:17,482 --> 01:27:19,151
Okay, so let's hear it.

1311
01:27:23,488 --> 01:27:27,743
The secret is
yours was the best kiss

1312
01:27:27,826 --> 01:27:30,328
that I've ever had
in my entire life.

1313
01:27:33,457 --> 01:27:35,167
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY) Um...

1314
01:27:35,333 --> 01:27:38,837
But we haven't kissed.

1315
01:27:42,340 --> 01:27:44,176
I mean,
not since the third grade.

1316
01:27:46,803 --> 01:27:49,765
Better get started then.
I don't have much time.

1317
01:28:21,505 --> 01:28:22,631
What was that for?

1318
01:28:23,882 --> 01:28:25,717
Because I wanted to.

1319
01:28:30,847 --> 01:28:32,140
I love you.

1320
01:28:48,406 --> 01:28:50,325
Juliet, I need to
talk to you.

1321
01:28:50,408 --> 01:28:52,077
Just for a second.
It's okay. Please?

1322
01:28:52,160 --> 01:28:53,829
Actually, I kind of have
somewhere I have to be.

1323
01:28:53,912 --> 01:28:55,288
I know what you have
planned for tonight

1324
01:28:55,747 --> 01:28:58,667
and I want you to know that you
don't have to do this. Okay?

1325
01:28:58,750 --> 01:28:59,835
You don't know anything.

1326
01:28:59,918 --> 01:29:02,045
I know that you have
something to tell me.

1327
01:29:02,420 --> 01:29:04,172
You have something
to tell all of us.

1328
01:29:04,256 --> 01:29:05,423
You're a bitch.

1329
01:29:07,759 --> 01:29:09,094
I have been a bitch.

1330
01:29:10,428 --> 01:29:12,430
I have been a bitch. We all
have been bitches, and I...

1331
01:29:12,556 --> 01:29:13,515
I'm sorry.
I have to go.

1332
01:29:13,598 --> 01:29:15,183
Listen to me. I'm trying
to tell you how sorry...

1333
01:29:15,267 --> 01:29:16,268
I am sorry.
You said that.

1334
01:29:16,393 --> 01:29:17,561
I'm sorry,
but I have to come with you.

1335
01:29:18,562 --> 01:29:19,855
Leave me alone!
I can't.

1336
01:29:19,938 --> 01:29:21,106
Sam!Sam!

1337
01:29:21,231 --> 01:29:23,108
Why did you run away from me? I
can't talk to you right now.

1338
01:29:23,191 --> 01:29:24,943
You've been ignoring me for
years, and then you...

1339
01:29:25,026 --> 01:29:27,362
You kiss me and then go back
to acting like I'm invisible?

1340
01:29:27,445 --> 01:29:29,114
I meant everything
that happened back there.

1341
01:29:29,239 --> 01:29:30,615
That's all I can say,
that I meant it,

1342
01:29:30,699 --> 01:29:32,033
and I wish it hadn't
taken me so long.

1343
01:29:32,117 --> 01:29:36,621
Sam, are you in trouble?
You can trust me.

1344
01:29:37,581 --> 01:29:39,040
You can trust me back.

1345
01:29:44,421 --> 01:29:45,422
Juliet!

1346
01:29:48,258 --> 01:29:49,259
Juliet!

1347
01:29:56,308 --> 01:29:57,684
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1348
01:29:57,809 --> 01:29:58,810
Juliet!

1349
01:30:09,821 --> 01:30:10,989
Juliet!

1350
01:30:12,324 --> 01:30:13,450
Juliet, don't!

1351
01:30:14,951 --> 01:30:16,161
Wait! Wait!

1352
01:30:16,745 --> 01:30:18,830
Why? What's going on?
Why are you following me?

1353
01:30:18,914 --> 01:30:20,916
Why can't you
leave me alone?

1354
01:30:20,999 --> 01:30:22,000
You don't want to die.

1355
01:30:23,251 --> 01:30:25,128
You want the pain
to stop.

1356
01:30:26,504 --> 01:30:28,423
Stop. You stop.

1357
01:30:28,506 --> 01:30:30,759
You don't know me.
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1358
01:30:30,842 --> 01:30:32,761
You could never understand.

1359
01:30:32,844 --> 01:30:34,763
SAMANTHA:
You have a choice, Juliet.

1360
01:30:34,846 --> 01:30:36,431
Not everybody gets that.

1361
01:30:36,514 --> 01:30:37,641
KENT: Sam!

1362
01:30:39,684 --> 01:30:40,977
Please let me help you.

1363
01:30:41,311 --> 01:30:42,771
Don't you get it?

1364
01:30:44,272 --> 01:30:45,523
You can't help me.

1365
01:30:47,192 --> 01:30:48,777
I can't be fixed.

1366
01:30:48,860 --> 01:30:50,445
You're not the one
who needs fixing.

1367
01:30:50,528 --> 01:30:52,030
There is nothing
wrong with you.

1368
01:30:52,155 --> 01:30:54,282
Don't let anyone tell you
that there is.

1369
01:30:56,993 --> 01:31:01,873
This is just a blip.
Your life will change, Juliet.

1370
01:31:03,291 --> 01:31:07,712
If you just hold on
for one more minute.

1371
01:31:15,387 --> 01:31:16,429
It's too late.

1372
01:31:17,555 --> 01:31:20,225
No, it's not.
It's never too late.

1373
01:31:21,476 --> 01:31:23,478
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

1374
01:31:25,397 --> 01:31:26,398
Juliet, stop!

1375
01:31:26,564 --> 01:31:28,066
(HORN BLARING)

1376
01:31:28,775 --> 01:31:30,902
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1377
01:31:40,870 --> 01:31:42,580
SAMANTHA: <i>Maybe for you
there's</i> a <i>tomorrow.</i>

1378
01:31:45,250 --> 01:31:49,921
<i>Maybe for you
there's 1,000 or 3,000</i>

1379
01:31:52,549 --> 01:31:53,550
<i>or 10.</i>

1380
01:31:53,675 --> 01:31:55,593
(IZZY AND SAMANTHA LAUGHING)

1381
01:31:56,761 --> 01:32:00,098
<i>But for some of us,
there's only today.</i>

1382
01:32:02,434 --> 01:32:04,602
<i>And what you do today matters.</i>

1383
01:32:05,603 --> 01:32:06,688
<i>In the moment</i>

1384
01:32:09,566 --> 01:32:11,317
<i>and maybe into infinity.</i>

1385
01:32:13,403 --> 01:32:15,030
<i>I see only my greatest hits.</i>

1386
01:32:19,909 --> 01:32:21,995
(INAUDIBLE)

1387
01:32:25,749 --> 01:32:27,792
<i>I see the things
I want to remember.</i>

1388
01:32:32,130 --> 01:32:34,174
<i>And be remembered for.</i>

1389
01:32:41,139 --> 01:32:44,350
<i>That's when I realized that
certain moments go on forever.</i>

1390
01:32:47,937 --> 01:32:50,482
<i>Even after they're over,
they still go on.</i>

1391
01:32:53,985 --> 01:32:55,320
<i>They are the meaning.</i>

1392
01:32:57,822 --> 01:32:58,823
JULIET: Sam?

1393
01:33:00,492 --> 01:33:01,785
Sam?

1394
01:33:04,329 --> 01:33:05,997
(CRYING) You saved me.

1395
01:33:08,833 --> 01:33:09,834
SAMANTHA: No.

1396
01:33:11,503 --> 01:33:13,296
<i>You saved me.</i>

1397
01:33:19,969 --> 01:33:22,013
(MUSIC PLAYING)

